Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g}, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, put the @Couscous{120%g} in a #bowl{}.

Pour in the boiled @Water for the Couscous{200%ml}, stir in half the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}.

Cover tightly with @cling film{}. Set aside for ~{10%minutes}.

In another bowl, combine the @Cider Vinegar{15%ml}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @Harissa Paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), remaining veg stock paste, @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Honey{15%g} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml} to the chicken.

> TIP: Put hardened honey into hot water for 1 min.

Simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Next, add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Fluff up the couscous and stir in the dressing. Share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the harissa chicken and spinach.

Crumble over the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%g}.

Enjoy!